    "en": {
      "title": "Dengue & COVID-19 risk, warning from health officials",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); The Ministry of Health says that there is a risk of dengue epidemic developing in Sri Lanka.",
        "Director of the National Dengue Control Unit, Dr. Sudath Samaraweera stated that in this month alone, about 8,200 dengue patients have been reported.",
        "Moreover, he said that over 43,000 dengue cases have also been reported within thie year, and this situation poses a risk of further growth.",
        "The Deputy Director of Health Services of the Ministry of Health, Dr. Hemantha Herath said that the number of COVID-19 patients being reported is also increasing.",
        "Dr. Herath mentioned that earlier, when only about 10 patients were being reported daily, now over 50 patients are being reported daily, and this situation should be taken more seriously, while emphasizing that the public to continue to adhere health guidelines.",
        "Govt and Govt approved private schools to resume activities on 25th July"
      ],
